PMID== 19348264
TI  == [two cases of anaerobic empyema including actinomyces].
AB  == we report 2 cases of empyema including actinomyces spp. case 1 was a 66-year-old  man with fever and left pleural effusion, actinomyces israelii and 2 other microbes were isolated. case 2 was a 52-year-old male inpatient who developed empyema during treatment of upper gastrointestinal bleeding. actinomyces odontolyticus and 3 other microbes were cultured in pleural effusion. empyema caused by actinomyces spp. is rare, in particular actinomyces odontolyticus is rarely isolated and only 4 cases have been reported in japan.
