TI  == actinomyces odontolyticus bacteremia.
AB  == we describe two immunosuppressed female patients with fever and actinomyces odontolyticus bacteremia, a combination documented once previously in an immunocompetent male patient. the patients were treated with doxycycline and clindamycin; these drugs, with beta-lactams, are effective treatment for a. odontolyticus infections.
