PMID== 10093534
TI  == ribotype diversity of actinomyces with similar intraoral tropism but different types of n-acetyl-beta-d-galactosamine binding specificity.
AB  == sixty-three isolates of actinomyces naeslundii genospecies 1 and 2 and actinomyces odontolyticus from three subjects clustered into 22 ribotypes. unique ribotypes were found in the subjects and within individual tissue sites (bucca, tooth and tongue). a odontolyticus ribotypes shared tongue-specific binding properties, while those of genospecies 1 and 2 from buccal and tooth surfaces shared different types of n-acetyl-beta-d-galactosamine binding specificity.
