PMID== 7146831
TI  == hepatic actinomycosis presenting as repeated cholestatic reactions.
AB  == a patient with hepatic actinomycosis caused by actinomyces odontolyticus is presented. the clinical course was characterized by 2 yr of episodic abdominal pains and fever together with marked acute elevations of serum alkaline phosphatase. the diagnosis escaped extensive laboratory studies, 2 liver biopsies and 1 laparotomy and was finally verified at a second laparotomy by histology and a positive culture. histopathology showed multiple small abscesses. no primary focus of infection was found. treatment with doxycycline was successful.
TIHT== 
