PMID== 495569
TI  == actinomycotic pulmonary abscess in an immunosuppressed patient.
AB  == the clinical history of a patient with rheumatoid arthritis and bacteriologic findings from a pulmonary abscess occurring during prednisone therapy are presented. direct transthoracic aspiration of the lesion yielded a pure culture of actinomyces odontolyticus. this is believed to be the first case of a deep visceral infection with this organism, an inhabitant of the normal mouth and gums. immunosuppression of the host probably played a role in establishment of the infection.
TIHT== 
